<p>Research conducted by Amalia Bastos, from the University of Auckland, suggests that the Kea can perform tasks which was previously thought only doable by apes. The <a href="https://www.nature.com/articles/s41467-020-14695-1" target="_blank">newest paper on their intellect</a></p>

